-- Bayern, Dortmund, Schalke Win to Stay Even at Top of Bundesliga
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-01-28T19:50:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-28/bayern-dortmund-schalke-win-to-stay-even-at-top-of-bundesliga.html
Bayern Munich, Dortmund and Schalke
all won to stay even on points at the top of German soccer’s
Bundesliga.  Mario Gomez  and  Arjen Robben  scored in Bayern’s 2-0 win
over Wolfsburg, and Shinji Kagawa had two goals as defending
champion Dortmund beat Hoffenheim 3-1. Schalke scored all of its
goals in the final 30 minutes, getting two from Ciprian Marica,
in beating Cologne 4-1.  The victories leave the three teams tied with 40 points.
Bayern lead the table on a superior goal difference, followed by
Dortmund and Schalke.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
